COVANTA PLYMOUTH RENEWABLE ENERGY, LLC
Reactive Power and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Covanta Plymouth Renewable Energy, LLC ("Covanta Plymouth") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Service") from its waste-to-energy generating facility located in Plymouth Meeting, Pennsylvania ("Facility") in the control area administered by the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") in order to assist in maintaining transmission voltage within acceptable limits on the PJM transmission system. This Reactive Service Tariff sets forth Covanta Plymouth's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Service from the facility pursuant to Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides for PJM to pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirements for Reactive Service.
Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This Reactive Service Tariff shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
REACTIVE SERVICE REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The total annual revenue requirement is $140,000.00.
The total monthly revenue requirement is $140,000.00 / 12 = $11,666.66.
